    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six with VarioCam Plus. This driver\u2019s spec includes the G96 six-speed manual transaxle and a factory limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a dual-row IMS bearing retrofit, a fresh air-oil separator (AOS), and a recently replaced water pump with a metal-blade impeller. The chassis is sharpened with Bilstein B8 dampers and Eibach progressive-rate springs, providing excellent lateral stability without compromising compliance. Recent Blackstone Labs oil analysis shows negligible wear metals. The exterior shows minor road rash consistent with enthusiast use, but the engine pulls strongly to its 7,200 RPM redline with no bore scoring symptoms. Shod in Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber with 70% tread remaining.",
